---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dylan Purbrick | Professional Reflection" activeTab="uni">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4">Professional Reflection</h1>
        <p class="text-brand-purple font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.4em]">Section_05 // Mechatronic Internship Evaluation</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-24">
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">01 // Expectations vs. Reality</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 text-slate-700">
                <div class="p-8 bg-slate-100/50 rounded-xl">
                    <p class="text-sm italic leading-relaxed">
                        "I suppose I expected the work to include elements of hands-on experience, the other workers to be friendly, and that this would be a great opportunity to expand my knowledge to further my career"[cite: 5].
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="p-8 bg-brand-purple/5 border-l-4 border-brand-purple rounded-r-xl">
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        The reality differed little from my expectations, though there was more paperwork than initially anticipated[cite: 7]. The working environment was more welcoming and less daunting than I could have thought[cite: 8].
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">02 // Key Lessons</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="font-black uppercase text-sm">Adaptability</h3>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">You must be able to manage effectively no matter how off-track a project goes[cite: 11].</p>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="font-black uppercase text-sm">Openness to Change</h3>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Being open to change and being adaptable go hand in hand in an industrial setting[cite: 10, 11].</p>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="font-black uppercase text-sm">Communication</h3>
                    <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Without communication, misunderstandings arise, leading to confusion and project derailment[cite: 12].</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-industrial-black text-white p-12 md:p-20 rounded-3xl">
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">03 // Value Proposition</h2>
            <p class="text-3xl font-black uppercase mb-12 leading-tight italic">
                "A versatile, process-oriented technical resource capable of translating complex engineering knowledge into clear, accessible documentation"[cite: 16].
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400">
                <ul class="space-y-4">
                    <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange">>></span> Systems Implementation (Autodesk Vault Pro) [cite: 19]</li>
                    <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange">>></span> Technical Communication (User Manuals) [cite: 20]</li>
                </ul>
                <ul class="space-y-4">
                    <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange">>></span> Process Improvement (Traceability Tables) [cite: 17, 18]</li>
                    <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange">>></span> Operational Consistency (Knowledge Sharing) [cite: 21]</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">04 // Career Influence</h2>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-12">
                This internship confirmed my foundational interest in hands-on mechanical design while revealing a significant strength in engineering process management[cite: 23]. Moving forward at Keith Engineering, I aim to integrate technical execution with process ownership[cite: 24, 25].
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 text-xs text-slate-500 leading-loose">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-black text-industrial-black uppercase mb-4">Technical Execution</h3>
                    <ul class="space-y-2">
                        <li>• CAD modeling: 1038 Press Shaft Bullnose [cite: 28]</li>
                        <li>• Workshop: Schenck Balancing rotor setup [cite: 29]</li>
                        <li>• Testing: Gearboxes and bearings [cite: 29]</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-black text-industrial-black uppercase mb-4">Process Management</h3>
                    <ul class="space-y-2">
                        <li>• Project Oversight: 1800 Cooker Wear Sleeves [cite: 30]</li>
                        <li>• Documentation: Centrifuge stripping user manuals [cite: 32]</li>
                        <li>• Templates: Customer evaluation reports [cite: 33]</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t border-slate-200 pt-24">
            <h2 class="text-brand-purple font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">05 // Internal Audit: Peer Feedback</h2>
            <div class="bg-white/50 p-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 space-y-12">
                <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed italic">
                    "Reflecting on my collaboration with Olivia, Muhaimin, and Eric, our team focused on the mechanical structure of a mechatronic system. Key takeaways included the importance of bridging the gap between technical CAD modeling and cost-effective material procurement."
                </p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-4">Technical Insight</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">My role at Keith Engineering allowed me to bring industry-standard QA practices to our student project, specifically in BOM verification.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-[10px] tracking-widest mb-4">Team Leadership</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Applied supervisor-level team management skills developed at the Lord Dudley Hotel to maintain project milestones[cite: 80, 81].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
